  <title>Behaviour on command exit</title>

  <p><app>Terminal</app> can perform the following operations when a command or a shell exits.</p>
  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>You have the following options to choose from:</p>
      <list>
        <item>
          <p><gui>Exit the terminal</gui></p>
        </item>
        <item>
          <p><gui>Restart the command</gui></p>
        </item>
        <item>
          <p><gui>Hold the terminal open</gui></p>
        </item>
      </list>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>To set any of these options, select <guiseq><gui
      style="menu">Edit</gui><gui style="menuitem">Preferences</gui><gui
      style="tab">Title and Command</gui></guiseq>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>From <gui
      stye="menu">When command exits</gui>, select the desired behaviour.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>

